<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,320,455]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,320,346]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Additional dorsocentral setae on presutural area absent.A pair of processes on male abdominal sternite VI slightly curved inward (
<figureCitation box="[420,508,356,383]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male abdominal sternite VIs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (B in anteroventral view, C in lateral view), C. stamenicola (Carson &amp; Okada) (D in anterior view) and all species of the C. cristata subgroup (A in ventral view, E‒R in anterior view): A, C. ecornuta sp. nov.; E, C. grandis sp. nov.; F, C. vieti sp. nov.; G, C. cristata de Meijere; H, C. matthewsi sp. nov.; I, C. sulawesiana Okada &amp; Yafuso; J, C. kinabaluana sp. nov.; K, C. kotana sp. nov.; L, C. sabahana sp. nov.; M, C. sarawakana sp. nov.; N, C. pistilicola (Carson &amp; Okada); O, C. xenalocasiae (Okada); P, C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada); Q, C. sumatrana sp. nov.; and R, C. leucocasiae sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766420/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 9L</figureCitation>
). Epandrium triangularly angled at posteroventral corner; anteroventral elongation as broad as cercus in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[546,652,392,419]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 24G</figureCitation>
). Female abdominal sternite VI wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[1213,1316,392,419]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 24E</figureCitation>
). Oviscapt broader than hypoproct, apically roundish in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[803,907,428,455]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 24K</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
