(♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,150,753]" box="[199,1260,150,177]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,150,176]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Description</emphasis>
(
<specimenCount box="[353,374,151,177]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[429,449,151,177]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
). Head. Supralateral setae outside prementum approximately 2 per side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,150,753]" box="[199,1093,187,213]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Thorax. Basal scutellar setae short, not reaching to half of apical scutellar setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,150,753]" box="[199,662,223,249]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Legs. Mid tibia with 2 apical, stout setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,150,753]" box="[199,840,259,285]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Abdomen. Female sternite IV as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[726,828,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 24E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,150,753]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Male terminalia. Epandrium with approximately 1 seta on lateral portion and 14–16 setae on posteroventral portion (
<figureCitation box="[249,356,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 24G</figureCitation>
). Median piece of subepandrial sclerite medially and anteriorly bilobed into long lobes; lateral pieces long, narrow. Cercus with 45–48 setae, extended below, apically forming small lobe with many small setae (
<figureCitation box="[160,264,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 24G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,150,753]" box="[199,909,438,465]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Female terminalia. Oviscapt with 14–15 ovisensilla (
<figureCitation box="[792,896,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 24K</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,150,753]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Indices (range of 
<specimenCount box="[393,442,475,501]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="male">10♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[495,546,475,501]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="female">10♀</specimenCount>
): FW/HW = 0.55–0.65, ch/o = 0.34–0.45, prorb = 0.83–1.04, rcorb = 0.22–0.47, vb = 0.25–0.39, dcl = (n/a), sctl = 0.51–0.77, sterno = 0.56–0.83, orbito = 0.48–0.77, dcp = 0.82–1.21, sctlp = 1.08–1.64, C = 1.62–2.56, 4c = 0.83–1.38, 4v = 1.31–1.94, 5x = 0.74–1.25, ac = 1.98–3.74, M = 0.25–0.56.
</paragraph>
